[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":130},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing\u002F":105,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing\u002F":114},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20190621\u002F4177225789\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":88,"date":89,"description":90,"extension":91,"lang":92,"meta":93,"navigation":94,"path":95,"readingMinutes":96,"seo":97,"standalone":98,"stem":99,"tags":100,"tldr":102,"updated":89,"url":103,"__hash__":104},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing.md","CoffeeScript Event Not Firing? It Was the Parentheses All Along","1001203691",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":81},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,38,48,53,56,60,67,73],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"I was writing some CoffeeScript the other day and hit a really weird one — my event handler just flat out wouldn't fire. So I'm jotting down what I tried and how I ended up fixing it, mostly so future me doesn't waste another afternoon on it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-problem","The problem",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"Here's how I had it written, and instead of working it kept throwing ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"TypeError: e is undefined",":",[17,33,34],{},[35,36],"img",{"alt":30,"src":37},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FtBANYvD.png",[17,39,40,41,44,45,31],{},"So I rewrote it using ",[28,42,43],{},"addEventListener"," instead — and now I got ",[28,46,47],{},"ReferenceError: e is not defined",[17,49,50],{},[35,51],{"alt":47,"src":52},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fve4OGoG.png",[17,54,55],{},"Same wall, different error message. Great.",[12,57,59],{"id":58},"the-fix","The fix",[17,61,62,63,66],{},"After talking it over with a coworker, the answer turned out to be embarrassingly simple — drop the parentheses on ",[28,64,65],{},"scrollTopClick()"," and everything just worked.",[17,68,69],{},[35,70],{"alt":71,"src":72},"scrollTopClick","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0Ix8hOa.png",[17,74,75,76,80],{},"The thing is, with the parens you're ",[77,78,79],"em",{},"calling"," the function and passing its return value as the handler. Without them you're passing the function itself, which is what the event actually wants. Easy to miss, annoying to debug.",{"title":82,"searchDepth":83,"depth":83,"links":84},"",2,[85,86,87],{"id":14,"depth":83,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":83,"text":23},{"id":58,"depth":83,"text":59},"JavaScript","2019-06-21 10:19:54","While writing some CoffeeScript I ran into a weird one — my event handler just wouldn't work. I kept getting \"TypeError: e is undefined\" and then \"ReferenceError: e is not defined.\" This is a quick note on what I tried and how I eventually fixed it.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing","1",{"title":6,"description":90},false,"en\u002FJavaScript\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing",[88,101],"CoffeeScript",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-event-not-firing\u002F","tVt7ZGUOq1Fpo8MNq9QxwVKn6gxIqrxS85zxwwIrgS0",{"newer":106,"older":110},{"url":107,"title":108,"date":109},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-ternary-operator\u002F","How Do You Write a Ternary Operator in CoffeeScript? (Spoiler: You Don't)","2019-06-21 11:49:07",{"url":111,"title":112,"date":113},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F20\u002Fcoffeescript-basics\u002F","CoffeeScript Basics: What This Compile-to-JS Language Actually Looks Like","2019-06-20 10:52:16",[115,120,125],{"url":116,"title":117,"date":118,"readingMinutes":119},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2026\u002F03\u002F10\u002Fweb-crypto-api-encryption-guide\u002F","No crypto Package, No Node.js — The Web Crypto API Does It All in the Browser","2026-03-10 09:45:08","9",{"url":121,"title":122,"date":123,"readingMinutes":124},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F08\u002Fjquery-why-it-declined\u002F","jQuery Was Once King — So Why Did It Fall Off?","2025-12-08 21:35:24","7",{"url":126,"title":127,"date":128,"readingMinutes":129},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F","What Are JavaScript Generator Functions (function*)? The Function You Can Pause and Resume","2025-12-05 13:40:31","5",1784010275855]